{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775834513783,"sessionID":"ses_28805857bffekUXF6uXjgQ92cZ","part":{"id":"prt_d77fa9d030018TAG1JhnZd614c","messageID":"msg_d77fa86a00019piOXeyrBJCDeI","sessionID":"ses_28805857bffekUXF6uXjgQ92cZ","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_5c5a1e0abbcb4654839d3ac8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure to understand:\n1. The overall directory layout\n2. Existing pkg/store directory if it exists\n3. pkg/common/types directory and its contents\n4. Any existing design documents or patterns\n5. Go module information (go.mod)\n6. Testing patterns used in the project\n\nFocus on understanding the project conventions, existing store implementations, and types that would be relevant for the Redis storage implementation (AR-013).\n\nReturn:\n- Project structure overview\n- Contents of pkg/store if it exists\n- Contents of pkg/common/types\n- Go module dependencies related to redis/valkey\n- Any existing design document patterns\n- Testing conventions","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2880554daffeNUYW0qRiDnYitj (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Overall Directory Layout\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n|-- go.mod                          # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n|-- go.sum\n|-- design.md                       # Root-level design doc (AR-012 session store)\n|-- proposal.md\n|-- project.md\n|-- delta-spec.md\n|-- test_spec.md\n|-- .sdd_prompt.md\n|-- coverage.out\n|\n|-- pkg/                            # Core Go packages\n|   |-- apis/\n|   |-- common/types/               # Type aliases (SandboxInfo, EntryPoint)\n|   |-- router/\n|   |-- store/                      # Redis/Valkey session store (9 files)\n|   |-- workloadmanager/handler/    # Sandbox models, lifecycle, CRUD\n|\n|-- changes/                        # Per-change design docs\n|   |-- AR-001/design.md ... AR-013/design.md\n|\n|-- ci-cd/design.md\n|-- cli-toolkit/design.md\n|-- code-execution/design.md\n|-- deployment/design.md\n|-- idle-cleanup/design.md\n|-- integrations/design.md\n|-- python-sdk/design.md\n|-- sandbox-orchestration/design.md\n|-- session-routing/design.md\n|-- session-store/design.md\n|\n|-- client-go/\n|-- testing/\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. pkg/store Directory Contents (9 files)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `store.go` | `Store` interface definition, `ErrNotFound` sentinel, `Storage()` singleton accessor |\n| `singleton.go` | `sync.Once`-based singleton, `initStore()` provider selection via `STORE_TYPE` env var |\n| `store_redis.go` | `redisStore` struct implementing `Store` using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` |\n| `store_valkey.go` | `valkeyStore` struct implementing `Store` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` |\n| `codec.go` | `encodeSandboxInfo()` / `decodeSandboxInfo()` JSON marshal/unmarshal helpers |\n| `singleton_test.go` | Singleton init tests: unsupported type, case insensitivity, concurrent access |\n| `store_redis_test.go` | Full Redis tests using `miniredis` (439 lines, 26 test functions) |\n| `store_valkey_test.go` | Valkey tests with struct-level validation and env-var panic tests (241 lines) |\n| `codec_test.go` | JSON encode/decode round-trip, invalid JSON, nil/empty edge cases |\n\n**Key Store Interface** (`store.go`):\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n**Singleton Pattern** (`singleton.go`):\n- Uses `sync.Once` for thread-safe lazy initialization\n- Provider selected via `STORE_TYPE` env var (case-insensitive, defaults to `\"redis\"`)\n- Supports `\"redis\"` and `\"valkey\"` providers\n- Constructor functions (`newRedisStore()`, `newValkeyStore()`) return `Store` interface directly\n\n**Redis Data Model**:\n- Session data: `session:{sessionID}` -> JSON string\n- Expiry index: `session:expiry` -> ZSET (score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`)\n- Activity index: `session:last_activity` -> ZSET (score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()`)\n\n---\n\n### 3. pkg/common/types Directory\n\n**File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/common/types/types.go`\n\nThis is a thin alias layer that re-exports types from `pkg/workloadmanager/handler`:\n\n```go\npackage types\n\nimport \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n\nconst (\n    AgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n    CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    SandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n    SandboxClaimKind    = \"SandboxClaim\"\n)\n\ntype SandboxInfo = handler.SandboxInfo\ntype EntryPoint = handler.EntryPoint\n```\n\n**Actual SandboxInfo definition** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go`):\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SessionID      string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxName    string       `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    SandboxID      string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    WorkloadName   string       `json:\"workloadName\"`\n    Namespace      string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Kind           string       `json:\"kind\"`\n    PodIP          string       `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n    EntryPoints    []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time    `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt      time.Time    `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status         string       `json:\"status\"`\n    LastActivityAt time.Time    `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n}\n\ntype EntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Go Module Dependencies (Redis/Valkey Related)\n\nFrom `go.mod` (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`, Go 1.25.0):\n\n**Direct dependencies:**\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client for redisStore |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.73 | Valkey client for valkeyStore |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | v2.37.0 | In-memory Redis for testing |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Test assertions (assert/require) |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT auth |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.22.0 | Metrics |\n| `k8s.io/api`, `k8s.io/apimachinery`, `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.22.2 | Kubernetes controller runtime |\n\n**Indirect Redis-related:**\n- `github.com/cespare/xxhash/v2` v2.3.0 (hashing, used by go-redis)\n- `github.com/dgryski/go-rendezvous` (rendezvous hashing for go-redis)\n- `go.uber.org/atomic` v1.11.0 (atomic operations)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Design Document Patterns\n\n**AR-013 Design Doc** (`changes/AR-013/design.md`): Currently a skeleton template with sections:\n- Architecture\n- Data Model\n- Interfaces\n- Error Handling\n- Testing Strategy\n\n**AR-012 Design Doc** (`design.md` / `changes/AR-012/design.md`): The root `design.md` is a fully fleshed-out English design document for the session store (687 lines). It follows this structure:\n\n1. **Architecture** - Purpose, provider selection flow (ASCII diagram), data flow diagram, package layout, dependencies table\n2. **Data Structures** - Interface definition, sentinel errors, constants, singleton state, struct definitions, key constants table\n3. **API Contracts** - Per-method specification tables (Redis vs Valkey behavior), ZSET score semantics, error handling matrix\n4. **Core Implementation** - Code snippets for singleton, constructors, key helpers, StoreSandbox, load helpers\n5. **Environment Variables** - Tables for Redis and Valkey env vars (required, defaults, notes)\n6. **Testing Strategy** - Unit test matrix tables, integration tests, mock strategy, gate requirements\n7. **Deployment Considerations** - Cluster slot affinity, password policy, ZSET growth, connection pooling\n8. **Implementation Steps** - Phased plan (Day 1-4)\n9. **Future Changes** - Priority table and known limitations\n\n**Design doc convention**: All change-specific docs live under `changes/{AR-XXX}/design.md`. The root `design.md` appears to serve as the canonical reference for AR-012.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Testing Conventions\n\n**Framework**: `github.com/stretchr/testify` with both `assert` and `require` packages.\n\n**Test File Naming**: `*_test.go` alongside implementation files, same package (`package store`).\n\n**Test Function Naming**: `Test{Component}_{Scenario}` pattern, e.g.:\n- `TestRedisStore_Ping`\n- `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success`\n- `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo`\n- `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember`\n\n**Mock Strategy**:\n- **Redis**: Uses `miniredis.Run()` for in-memory Redis-compatible server\n- **Valkey**: Tests use bare struct instantiation (no mock client) for input validation tests; constructor tests use `recover()` to catch `klog.Fatal` panics\n\n**Test Helper Pattern**:\n```go\nfunc newTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) (*redisStore, *miniredis.Miniredis) {\n    t.Helper()\n    mr, err := miniredis.Run()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    t.Cleanup(func() { mr.Close() })\n    cli := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()})\n    t.Cleanup(func() { cli.Close() })\n    return &redisStore{cli: cli, ...}, mr\n}\n```\n\n**Fixture Pattern**:\n```go\nfunc testSandboxInfo(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    now := time.Now().UTC()\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SessionID: sessionID,\n        SandboxName: \"test-sandbox\",\n        // ... all fields populated\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Environment Variable Cleanup**: Tests that modify env vars always restore them with `defer`:\n```go\noriginal := os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\")\ndefer os.Setenv(\"STORE_TYPE\", original)\n```\n\n**Assertion Patterns**:\n- `require.NoError(t, err)` for fatal errors that stop the test\n- `assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrNotFound)` for sentinel error checking\n- `assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"substring\")` for error message validation\n- `assert.Same(t, first, s)` for pointer identity (singleton tests)\n- `assert.Len(t, result, N)` for collection size\n\n**Concurrency Testing**: Uses `sync.WaitGroup` + channel to verify singleton thread-safety.\n\n**Gate Requirements** (from design.md):\n1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n5. No sensitive data in logs\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2880554daffeNUYW0qRiDnYitj","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775834409762,"end":1775834513780}}}}
